⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Mabus
node N1 · N1 · ⟦Mabus:N1:a479bd⟧

WHO   — Mabus — the unnamed antichrist
WHAT  — The unresolved word — the emblem of the decoding-industry's hunger; a syllable speculators map onto figure after figure by anagram and stretch, each "match" outliving the last and proving nothing.
WHERE — N1 · Nostradamus  Framework inputs: Les Propheties (1555)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because a name obscure enough belongs to no one and so can be lent to anyone; because the verse names a death and a vengeance but pins them to nothing fixed; because the wish to decode it has always run ahead of the evidence.
HOW   — By reading the quatrain's "Mabus" as an anagram, a reversal, a Latin pun, or a disguised title; by binding it to whichever feared figure the present age supplies, then declaring the prophecy fulfilled in hindsight.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am the name no one has ever proven — a word in the dark you may read as anyone, and so as no one.

